<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Populus tremuloides </i>is adapted to fire. New sprouts develop from adventitious roots when fire kills the old stems. Individual stems may live up to 150 years. Seedlings also readily colonize after fire, clear cutting, or other disturbances. Reduction of surface fire in <i>P. tremuloides </i>understories and adjacent conifer stands has increased conifer invasion in stands in California.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Medium (10-100 years)
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
